      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a weird loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually turning. any idea what's wrong or what i should look at? also is it safe to open the panel?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That humming noise while the fan stays still usually means the compressor is trying to start but the motor is stuck or the capacitor is failing. Before you open anything, check if you can reset the circuit breaker or disconnect the outdoor unit for a minute to clear any electrical lockout. Regarding your safety question, yes, you can open the panel if the unit is completely unplugged and the breaker is off, but be aware that capacitors inside can still hold a lethal charge for a few minutes even after powering down. If you are unsure about electrical components or the noise persists after a reset, it is best to call a professional technician.",
